citation.excerpt: [1] Redmon, Joseph, et al. "You only look once: Unified, real-time object detection." Proceedings of the IEEE conference on computer vision and pattern recognition. 2016. (https://arxiv.org/abs/1506.02640)

description.excerpt: Implementation of YOLO v1 object detector in PyTorch. Full tutorial can be found here in korean.
Only Pascal VOC datasets are supported for now.

installation.excerpt: Tested under Python 3.6, PyTorch 0.4.1 on Ubuntu 16.04, Windows10.

invocation.excerpt:
main.py --mode train -data_path where/your/dataset/is --class_path ./names/VOC.names --num_class 20 --use_augmentation True --use_visdom True 
main.py  --mode test --data_path where/your/dataset/is --class_path ./names/VOC.names --num_class 20 --checkpoint_path your_checkpoint.pth.tar
